HABITAT. — Frequently found in old farms, this species occupies grassland, tufty gramineous areas, and cultivated fields. It is only uncommonly spotted in dry grasses. According to many studies,
T. nasuta
is almost always correlated with Graminae crops and steppe environments ( Usmani 2008 ;
Moussi et al. 2011
).

